President Trump delivered remarks in the East Room of the White House celebrating the confirmation of more than 150 federal judges by his administration and Republicans in Congress. He praised the judges as "gifted scholars, respected jurists, and finest legal minds," and emphasized the importance of appointing judges who adhere to the original meaning of the Constitution. The President also criticized left-wing activists for using nationwide injunctions to stop the enforcement of executive actions and duly enacted laws. He thanked Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell and Senator Lindsey Graham for their support in confirming the judges. The President concluded by pledging to continue nominating highly qualified judges who love the Constitution and will ensure equal justice for all.